"""Cavern prop sprites: floor debris (b495-498) + room contents (b497-499).

Pixel-art props stamped onto the drawn cavern by the procedural
renderer (cavern_render.py).

CAVERN_PROPS -- ambient debris scattered on PLAIN floors (bones,
rubble, webs, mushrooms, flora...). Checker-keyed, defringed, webs
matted translucent, capped 40px.

ROOM_PROPS -- identity props per THEMED room type, drawn at a seeded
off-center spot (b499: real art from the generated prompt sheets --
treasure chests, anvil+forge, market stalls, skull doors, shrine
statues, crystal ball, portal circles, taxidermy bench, bookshelf,
alchemy gear, weapon racks, stone stairs). U/D draw centered and
larger (fixtures); E draws nothing; M is glyph-only (entities get
glyphs, rooms get props). Capped 48px.

Debris deliberately excludes anything that reads as LOOT so
decorations never bait a tap; room props deliberately INCLUDE
reward-ish art (chests) because those rooms ARE interactable.
"""

